    <title>Reviews and Essays</title>
    <blockquote>
      <title>
        <ulink url="http://www.itworld.com/mobile-wireless/179875/are-android-and-linux-same-thing">ITworld/Brian Proffitt: Are Android and Linux the same thing?</ulink>
      </title>
      <para>I&apos;ve knocked the sand out of my keyboard, applied aloe to my sunburned skin, and am trying to apply my refreshed and relaxed brain to the following conundrum:</para>
      <para>Is Android Linux?</para>
      <para><emphasis role="bold">[Also see: <ulink url="http://www.itworld.com/software/140528/android-violates-linux-license-experts-claim">Android violates Linux license, experts claim</ulink>]</emphasis></para>
      <para>There are arguments for each side, naturally. The biggest for Android being Linux is, of course, the fact that the kernel for the Linux operating system and the Android operating system are very nearly one and the same. Not completely the same, mind you, but Android&apos;s kernel is directly derived from Linux. (...)</para>
<!-- ($ ld: 8.7.11 sat $) -->    </blockquote>
